<section xml:id="C7.S6">
<title>Series Expansions</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C7.S6.SS1">
<title>Power Series</title>           
<para xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="7.6.1" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E1">\operatorname{erf}z=\frac{2}{\sqrt{\pi}}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}z^{2n +1}}{n!(2n+1)}</Math> ,, <Math equation-number="7.6.2" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E2">\operatorname{erf}z=\frac{2}{\sqrt{\pi}}e^{-z^{2}}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{2^{ n}z^{2n+1}}{1\cdot 3\cdots(2n+1)},</Math> , <Math equation-number="7.6.3" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E3">w\left(z\right)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(iz)^{n}}{\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}n+1 \right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="7.6.4" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E4">C\left(z\right)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}(\frac{1}{2}\pi)^{2n}}{(2n)!( 4n+1)}z^{4n+1},</Math> <Math equation-number="7.6.5" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E5">C\left(z\right)=\cos\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z^{2}\right)\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac {(-1)^{n}\pi^{2n}}{1\cdot 3\cdots(4n+1)}z^{4n+1}+\sin\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z^{ 2}\right)\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}\pi^{2n+1}}{1\cdot 3\cdots(4n+3)}z^{ 4n+3}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="7.6.6" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E6">S\left(z\right)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}(\frac{1}{2}\pi)^{2n+1}}{(2n+ 1)!(4n+3)}z^{4n+3}</Math> , <Math equation-number="7.6.7" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E7">S\left(z\right)=-\cos\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z^{2}\right)\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{(-1)^{n}\pi^{2n+1}}{1\cdot 3\cdots(4n+3)}z^{4n+3}+\sin\left(\tfrac{1}{2} \pi z^{2}\right)\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}\pi^{2n}}{1\cdot 3\cdots(4n+1 )}z^{4n+1}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1.s4">
The series in this subsection and in §7.6(ii) converge for all finite values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S6.SS1.p1.m1">|z|</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C7.S6.SS2">
<title>Expansions in Series of Spherical Bessel Functions</title>           
<para xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p1.s1">
For the notation see §§10.47(ii) and 18.3.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="7.6.8" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E8">\operatorname{erf}z=\frac{2z}{\sqrt{\pi}}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}(-1)^{n}\left({ \mathsf{i}^{(1)}_{2n}}\left(z^{2}\right)-{\mathsf{i}^{(1)}_{2n+1}}\left(z^{2} \right)\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="7.6.9" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E9">\operatorname{erf}\left(az\right)=\frac{2z}{\sqrt{\pi}}e^{(\frac{1}{2}-a^{2})z ^{2}}\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}T_{2n+1}\left(a\right){\mathsf{i}^{(1)}_{n}}\left( \tfrac{1}{2}z^{2}\right), if -1\leq a\leq 1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="7.6.10" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E10">C\left(z\right)=z\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\mathsf{j}_{2n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z^{2} \right),</Math> <Math equation-number="7.6.11" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S6.E11">S\left(z\right)=z\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\mathsf{j}_{2n+1}\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi z^{ 2}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C7.S6.SS2.p2.s1">
